  "prompt": "Where do I get all episodes of dragon ball Kai in English?",
  "response": "Dragon Ball Kai, also known as Dragon Ball Z Kai, can be found through various streaming services and platforms. As of the latest information, you can watch the English-dubbed episodes on:\n\n1. **Funimation**: Funimation is one of the primary licensors of Dragon Ball Kai and offers the entire series for streaming with an English dub.\n\n2. **Crunchyroll**: Crunchyroll has integrated many Funimation titles since their partnership, so it's worth checking if Dragon Ball Kai is available there.\n\n3. **Amazon Prime Video**: You can purchase episodes or the complete seasons directly from Amazon, both in English dub and original Japanese with subtitles.\n\n4. **Hulu**: Hulu occasionally offers Dragon Ball Kai episodes, so it might be another platform to explore if you have a subscription.\n\nPlease note that the availability can change, so it's always a good idea to check these platforms directly for the current status. Additionally, DVDs and Blu-rays of Dragon Ball Z Kai can also be purchased from online retailers like Amazon if you prefer physical copies.",
